  "base_path": "/workplace-temperatures",
  "content_id": "dd72f66d-4240-4ee5-ab88-c2abca2b35b8",
  "description": "There is no law for a minimum or maximum temperature, but during working hours the temperature in all workplaces inside buildings must be reasonable\r\n",
  "details": {
    "body": "\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>During working hours the temperature in all indoor workplaces must be reasonable.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>There’s no law for minimum or maximum working temperatures, eg when it’s too cold or too hot to work.</p>\n\n<p>However, guidance suggests a minimum of 16ºC or 13ºC if employees are doing physical work.</p>\n\n<p>There’s no guidance for a maximum temperature limit.</p>\n\n<p>Employers must stick to health and safety at work law, including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>keeping the temperature at a comfortable level</li>\n  <li>providing clean and fresh air</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Employees should talk to their employer if the workplace temperature isn’t comfortable.</p>\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ]
  },
